.TH secauthmigrate 8
.SH NAME
.PP
secauthmigrate \- Convert ULTRIX auth(5) authentication data to authcap(4) authentication data  (Enhanced Security)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\*L/usr/sbin/secauthmigrate \*O[\*Voptions\*O] \*Vfiles\*O
.PP
\&... \*L| /usr/sbin/secauthmigrate \*O[\*Voptions\*O]\*L \-\*O
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "secauthmigrate"
.iX "authentication data migration"
.iX "migration, security"
The
\*Lsecauthmigrate\*O utility reads records from the specified \*Lfiles\*O
or from standard input (\-).
These records must be formatted according to the ULTRIX \*Lauth\*O(5) format.
These can be generated by \*Lgetauth\*O on ULTRIX, or (for
the Hesiod/BIND master host) can be found in \*L/var/dss/namedb/src/auth\*O.
For each authentication record found, \*Lsecauthmigrate\*O will attempt to find
a matching username record for the given UID.  If that translation can be
performed, an \*Lauthcap\*O(4) entry for the extended profile information for
that user is created from the data in the input record.  If the
extended profile entry already exists, then the converted entry is
left in \*L/tcb/files/auth/?/\*Vusername\*L:ULT\*O rather than
overwrite the entry in \*L/tcb/files/auth/?/\*Vusername\*O.
.PP
If ROOTDIR is defined, it is used instead of \*L/\*O as the root of the
directory tree when creating the \*L/tcb/files/auth/?/*\*O files.
.SH FLAGS
.PP
.IP "\-v"
Indicate successful conversions on standard output.
.IP "\-U"
Give a long usage message.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
\*LFailed to find name for UID # \*Vxxxx\*L -- skipped\*O
.br
No BSD style (\*L/etc/passwd\*O or NIS data) account exists. If you need this account, create a BSD style account and run \*Lsecauthmigrate\*O again.
.PP
\*LExisting file for \*Vusername\*L -- conversion saved in /tcb/files/auth/?/\*Vusername\*L:ULT\*O
.br
Extended profile already exists. Compare the files to determine the differences.
If the differences are not related to the password, use the \*LXIsso\*O 
program to update the existing file.
If the differences are related to related to the password,
diable logins and edit the \*L/tcb/files/auth/?/\*Vusername\*O file.
.PP
\*Lsecauthmigrate -- unrecognized option '${opt}'\*O
.br
The option you provided was not recognized.
The options are \*L\-v\*O and \*L\-U\*O.
.PP
\*LUsage: secauthmigrate [options] files\*O
.br
\*L  \  (Try secauthmigrate \-U for help.)\*O
.br
The \*L\-U\*O option provides extensive help.
.SH FILES
.PP
\*L${ROOTDIR}/tcb/files/auth/?/*\*O
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP
\*Lauthcap\*O(4), \*Lprpasswd\*O(4)
.PP
\*Lauth\*O(5) and \*Lgetauth\*O(8) on ULTRIX
.PP
\*EEnhanced Security\*O
.EQ
